About this item

  • A TRUE MULTI-TASKER: One drop of Vibriance Super C Vitamin C Facial Serum nourishes your skin with a powerful combination of skin nutrients. This multi-tasking vitamin C serum combines several products into one, making you look more vibrant than ever.
  • NOT JUST WATER: When it comes to vitamin C face serum, the ordinary face serum is watered down and ineffective. Our formula, on the other hand, is a high-quality and highly concentrated vitamin C serum. The base ingredient in Vibriance Super C Serum is made from evaporated lemons, while other brands’ base ingredient is simply tap water.
  • QUICK ABSORPTION: Vibriance Super C penetrating face serum - vitamin C rich and contains a unique active lock delivery system. This helps our active ingredients moisturize your skin and remain within the top levels as a reservoir for maximum nourishment.
  • FOR ALL SKIN TYPES: Vibriance Super C anti-aging vitamin c face serum was thoughtfully developed for all skin types, including those with extremely sensitive skin. We set out to create the best vitamin c serum for face, and developed this incredible formula of face serum for women and men that is proven effective, high-quality, affordable and easy-to-use.
  • MADE IN THE USA: Often imitated but never duplicated, the original Vibriance Super C Vitamin C Serum was established in 2015. Vibriance is dedicated to providing premium skin care products transparently backed by science. All of our products are proudly made in the USA.

      Important information

      Safety Information

      Keep out of reach of children. Protect from heat, light, and moisture.

      Indications

      Vibriance Vitamin C Serum reduces the appearance of wrinkles, melasma and age spots and gives your skin a healthy glow.

      Ingredients

      Lemon Fruit Water, Butylene Glycol, Cyclopentasiloxane, Dimethicone, PEG-8, Isododecane, Water, Polysilicone-11, 3-O-Ethyl Ascorbic Acid, Sodium Hyaluronate, Glucomannan, Orange Peel Oil, Hexylresorcinol, Acetyl Glucosamine, Allantoin, Panthenol, Tocopheryl Acetate, Caffeine, Decyl Glucoside, Coco Caprylate/Caprate, Polyacrylate-13, Polyisobutene, Polysorbate 20, Phenoxyethanol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Ethylhexyl Palmitate, Trihydroxystearin, Acrylates/ C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, PPG-12/SMDI Copolymer, Disodium EDTA, Triethanolamine.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Amazon Customer
      4 Stars
      Awesome scent but...
      I had read a review that the product did not extend through the whole container, but I did not find that too surprising. What I did find surprising was just have little of the container actually contained product. Once the pump stops working, I usually take the top off to see if there is some left that can be reached and used. Well, I did just that this morning and what I found was unexpected, to say the least! Nearly 2/3 of the container is just that - CONTAINER. Empty container. It's 1 thing to provide a small bottle and you know what you have. Instead you're given a "weight." There is no way to determine how much product is in "1 oz" or how far it will go, how long it will last. This is a marketing tactic used constantly by many different products, but I find specifically with make up/skin care. This, however, of all the cosmetic products I have used over the years (and there have been many, I assure you!) is the worst! The product fills only of the actual container about 1/2". The smell is awesome, and maybe my skin feels a little smoother, but the it does not do what it proposes and if you considered how much of the product you receive in this container vs. a jar of another - well, you are probably paying more for this stuff. I can find that citris scent elsewhere for a lot less. I will not be buying this again! Note - tried to upload a picture, but could not get it to upload. If I can, I will edit at a later time.3/10/24 While I still feel this is pricey for the amount given and the amount of time it lasts, I concede that, as anything else, it can take longer with some to see results. I am trying the product for a second month. I do feel my skin is softer but am working on marionette lines and those around my mouth. As many know, these are deep wrinkles and not just fine lines. I will check back in another month.

      Deborah Edelen
      3.0 out of 5 stars Can cause serious irritation
      Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2024
      Size: 1 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)Verified Purchase
      First of all, I have many years of experience working for prestige cosmetic companies. I know my ingredients. There are two kinds of Vitamin C products. One can boost radiance and give smoothness. Many however can cause irritation as they are acidic and, as with AHAs, exfoliate chemically. I thought that this product seemed like a radiance formulation, and when I tried it, it did have that smoothing, radiance-enhancing effect and the orangey smell. However soon after I started using it, I had a bout of redness, itchiness, inflammation and peeling that I blamed on dehydration, winter dryness and the flu. I had gone back to my previous routine, and forgotten all about this. I then saw an ad touting it as a miracle for wrinkles and found it in the back of my cabinet. In two days, my skin is again peeling, irritated, inflamed, red and itchy. I now know it was the cause. This is not helpful to aging, as nothing looks worse than red, inflamed, patchy skin and it is damaging. Furthermore, this is not entirely due to a sensitive skin type, but the acidic nature of the ingredients. The lack of reviews mentioning this are simply because it is not explained, people don't know what the cause is, and it feels soothing going on. Other than exfoliating, it will do nothing for wrinkles, and it may irritate. The pump also contains much less than it appears.
